def.continued:
but does not include an election donation if particulars of the donation
                    are given in an election return that has been lodged with the appropriate
                    authority;

subsection.def:
conduct (行為) engaged
                in by a person may be corrupt or illegal conduct even though the way in which it
                affects another person is only indirect;

corporate elector (團體選民) has the same meaning as in section 3(1) of the
                Legislative Council Ordinance (Cap.
                542);

election appeal (選舉上訴) means an appeal to a Revising Officer under section 39
                of the Schedule to the Chief Executive Election Ordinance (Cap. 569);
                (Amended 21 of 2001 s. 77)

Election Committee (選舉委員會) means the Election Committee constituted
                under section 8(1) of the Chief Executive Election Ordinance (Cap. 569);
                (Amended 21 of 2001 s. 77)

paragraph.content:
any money given to or in respect of the candidate or candidates for the
                        purpose of meeting, or contributing towards meeting, the election expenses
                        of the candidate or candidates;

promoting the election of the
                        candidate;
                        or

any person who is appointed under an electoral law to exercise
                        functions in connection with an
                        election;

subsection.def:
notice (通知) includes
                leaflet, circular, bill, booklet, placard and poster;
                (Amended 11 of 2012 s. 25)

publish (發布) means
                print, exhibit, distribute, post up, publicly announce or make publicly known by any
                other means, and includes continue to publish;

